it at any given time.

32:00.105 --> 32:02.242
But you must've seen
what happened, right?

32:02.276 --> 32:04.246
Please...

32:04.280 --> 32:06.985
Paint me a word picture.

32:07.019 --> 32:10.626
It was my finest hour,
and I couldn't be there.

32:10.660 --> 32:12.530
Your finest hour?

32:12.564 --> 32:15.135
Everyone went crazy.

32:15.168 --> 32:16.237
They were
tearing each other apart.

32:16.270 --> 32:18.108
"Everyone"?

32:18.141 --> 32:20.479
Every person who watched
was affected?

32:20.513 --> 32:22.483
The response was 100%?

32:25.155 --> 32:28.161
‐Unbelievable.
‐Our friends are dead,
and you're talking

32:28.194 --> 32:30.165
like it's an experiment
or a game score.

32:30.198 --> 32:32.002
It's neither. It's a...

32:32.035 --> 32:34.641
It's an experience.
It's a cinematic happening.

32:34.674 --> 32:36.545
A horror movie

32:36.578 --> 32:39.016
where the horror
isn't on‐screen.

32:39.049 --> 32:40.152
It's in the audience.

32:41.487 --> 32:43.559
Try to appreciate
what I'm talking about. Come on!

32:43.592 --> 32:45.262
I mean, you two must be

32:45.295 --> 32:47.166
film buffs or you wouldn't
have been there last night,

32:47.199 --> 32:50.305
so you must know about the, uh,
subliminals in The Exorcist?

32:56.718 --> 32:58.722
William Friedkin

32:58.756 --> 33:02.129
cut two frames of a demon's face
into reel six.

33:03.431 --> 33:05.570
People were throwing up
in the aisles.

33:05.603 --> 33:08.041
There were cases
of women going into labor.

33:08.074 --> 33:10.212
One gave birth
right in the theater.

33:10.245 --> 33:12.082
People thought
they were possessed,

33:12.115 --> 33:13.586
and all because of two frames,

33:13.619 --> 33:15.088
two little frames,

33:15.121 --> 33:17.159
and some creative sound.

33:17.192 --> 33:19.096
In certain spots,

33:19.129 --> 33:21.100
we mixed in the sound
of an angry beehive.

33:21.133 --> 33:23.071
Oh, really got
on people's nerves.

33:23.104 --> 33:26.210
Guess whose idea it was,
the subliminals.

33:26.244 --> 33:27.547
Yours?

33:28.582 --> 33:30.418
Second assistant cutter.

33:30.452 --> 33:32.322
We changed film forever.

33:32.356 --> 33:34.326
We should've won Best Picture
that year.

33:34.360 --> 33:36.698
You know what did? The Sting.

33:36.732 --> 33:38.201
It was a travesty!

33:38.234 --> 33:39.738
I couldn't let that stand.

33:39.771 --> 33:41.608
I had to take it
to the next level.

33:41.642 --> 33:45.215
So I raised money
for my own movie.

33:45.248 --> 33:47.620
I was after the recipe, you see.

33:47.654 --> 33:51.494
The‐the universal combination
of image and sound

33:51.528 --> 33:53.097
that would trigger

33:53.131 --> 33:54.801
the fear center
of every human brain.

33:54.834 --> 33:57.239
I studied
intrusive memory formation,

33:57.272 --> 33:59.578
the CIA hijinks with MK‐Ultra.

33:59.611 --> 34:01.748
Did you know flashes
of 330 hertz

34:01.782 --> 34:06.625
can trigger seizures
even in people without epilepsy?

34:06.658 --> 34:08.596
I applied everything I learned

34:08.629 --> 34:12.236
like Edison
creating the light bulb.

34:12.269 --> 34:14.541
I used thousands of combinations

34:14.574 --> 34:17.212
until one day, it happened.

34:25.696 --> 34:27.800
I gave my editor some notes,

34:27.834 --> 34:30.272
and I came by
to see what she'd done.

34:30.305 --> 34:32.075
‐
‐Lanie?

34:43.565 --> 34:45.101
Lanie, what are you...

34:48.542 --> 34:51.280
They put her away.
Combination of overwork

34:51.314 --> 34:53.251
and drugs.

34:53.284 --> 34:55.656
I knew the real score.

34:55.690 --> 34:59.330
I knew the film was ready.

35:00.332 --> 35:01.835
I found a distributor.

35:01.868 --> 35:04.139
Opened in one regional venue.

35:04.173 --> 35:06.645
Just a special engagement
to build word of mouth.

35:06.678 --> 35:08.448
And the response

35:08.481 --> 35:10.519
was beyond my expectations.

35:10.553 --> 35:12.456
Even after what happened,

35:12.489 --> 35:14.527
people wanted to see it.

35:14.561 --> 35:16.330
Until...

35:16.364 --> 35:19.671
a certain senator's spouse
turned her attention to me.

35:19.704 --> 35:21.541
It's a letter

35:21.575 --> 35:26.150
stating they've agreed
to pull your movie immediately.

35:28.388 --> 35:30.358
Not only that.

35:30.392 --> 35:33.632
They're going to destroy
every print in existence.

35:33.666 --> 35:35.435
You bitch!

35:37.205 --> 35:38.809
‐
‐Somebody stop him!

35:39.878 --> 35:41.480
‐
‐I'm gonna kill you.

35:41.515 --> 35:43.184
I'm gonna kill you!

35:43.217 --> 35:47.192
I won't stop until the whole
world sees my movie!

35:48.896 --> 35:51.334
They charged me with assault.

35:51.367 --> 35:53.237
They put me away for 15 years.

35:53.271 --> 35:55.442
A society
that locks up its artists

35:55.475 --> 35:57.513
doesn't deserve to survive.

35:57.547 --> 35:59.918
It deserves to burn. So,

35:59.951 --> 36:02.924
like a monk,
I spent every minute of my time

36:02.957 --> 36:05.362
gathering every piece
of information I could

36:05.395 --> 36:08.334
to fix and to refine the recipe.

36:09.771 --> 36:11.908
And when I got out, I applied it

36:11.942 --> 36:13.912
to a workprint
that I'd squirreled away.

36:13.946 --> 36:15.750
And the rest...

36:15.783 --> 36:17.352
is history.

36:19.791 --> 36:22.396
Okay. I know
you're angry right now,

36:22.429 --> 36:24.233
but try to appreciate
the big picture.

36:24.266 --> 36:26.270
You were a witness to history.

36:26.303 --> 36:29.376
You can retire
to the lecture circuit.

36:29.410 --> 36:30.913
You'll never have to work
another day.

36:30.946 --> 36:34.521
Take the win
and get on with your lives.

36:34.554 --> 36:37.359
You two look like nice kids.

36:37.392 --> 36:39.263
We saw some of your movie.

36:39.296 --> 36:41.535
The both of us.

36:41.568 --> 36:44.507
Wasn't enough to make us crazy.

36:44.541 --> 36:46.778
But enough to make us do this.

36:50.418 --> 36:51.922
How's that fear center doing?

36:51.955 --> 36:54.359
‐You bitch.
‐Where's the print?

36:54.393 --> 36:56.297
